    • Field Detail

      • openMIMEEntities

        protected Map<String,MIMEEntity> openMIMEEntities
        This variable tracks the current MIME entity. There are some important rules when working with MIME items: 1) you have to disable MIME-conversion in session
        2) you must not access the document with the Item interface (otherwise the server may crash)
        3) you should not access more than one MIME entity at once (otherwise the server may crash)
        4) you MUST call closeMIMEEntities() after a MIME operation (otherwise the server may crash)
        this means: if you have opened a MIME item do NOTHING with this document until you call closeMimeEntities()

      • appendItemValue

        public Item appendItemValue(String name,
                            Object value,
                            boolean unique)
        Description copied from interface: Document
        Appends a value to an existing Item, with an option to only add it if the value does not already exist in the Item.

        The method is only useful if a single value is being appended, because it use containsValue(value) This allows the developer to avoid duplicate values but also avoid unnecessary saves with transactional processing.

        Specified by:
        appendItemValue in interface Document
        Parameters:
        name - String Item name
        value - Object value
        unique - Boolean whether to only add the value if the Item does not already hold the value
        Returns:
        Item being updated

      • containsValues

        public boolean containsValues(Map<String,Object> filterMap)
        Description copied from interface: Document
        Receives a Map where the key is an Item name and the value is a value to look for in the relevant Item. If one key/value pair matches (so one of the Items contains the value to look for), the method returns true. HashMap check = new Map(); check.put("Form","Person"); check.put("FirstName","Fred"); return doc.containsValues(check);

        Returns true if the relevant Document's Form item contains "Person" or the Document's FirstName item contains "Fred".
        Returns false if the relevant Document's Form does not contain "Person" and the Document's FirstName item does not contain "Fred".

        Specified by:
        containsValues in interface Document
        Parameters:
        filterMap - Map to check
        Returns:
        Boolean whether one of the items contains a value
